        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 14 at 3:14PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 314 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Texas Creek, or 47 miles west of Pueblo, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Texas Creek, Canon City, Silver Cliff, and Westcliffe.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
